dor.cx is a personal social network built on your email box. enter your email login below to get started. your credentials, posts and content aren't stored here - you hold onto those. [more info]
we couldn't log you in automatically. please check your password or supply more details about your email account (IMAP).
great, you are all signed in to your email box.
now we're going to build the dorcx subfolders inside your mailbox. this is where we'll store all the posts you send and receive from people. everything will be in a subfolder called "dorcx'".

building your contacts/friends list from your existing emails...
* friends who are already dorcx users are flagged as such.

* with those friends you can: follow their public stream, send 'friend' request for their friend stream (or any other private stream they are publishing), send private message, see a list of their streams etc.
* friends who are dorcx users show their dorcx avatar.
* non-dorcx users might have a gravatar, otherwise generic icon. you can send them private messages, group messages, or invite them to use dorcx (maybe? too irritating/intrusive?).
* group mode lets you single-click to create a new group out of people you have selected.

* contacts are ordered by frequency of interaction by default but you can "favorite" contacts or whatever. this algorithm might change later if people give dorcx access to other stuff like rss feeds, twitter streams, facebook, etc.
now let's take a look at your emails to figure out your contacts list and the people you most frequently interact with.
is that ok?

* here you can select 'friends' (which is the private stream), or you can select 'group' or 'personal' which shows an input box to put in names/emails kinda like google plus does. when 'group' is selected a list of groups you most recently interacted with appears as a dropdown too.
